radiographic_examinations.findings: Bibasilar atelectasis, right atrium markedly enlarged, cholelithiasis without evidence of cholecystitis, inflamed diverticulum of the sigmoid colon with surrounding soft tissue stranding and wall thickening, trace amount of free fluid in the pelvis, bilateral renal hypodensities suggestive of cysts, Schmorl's node with moderate superior compression deformity of the L5 vertebral body.
